        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="1384" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1384">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/9–1949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-19T19:00:00-04:00">September 19, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1916. Pls inform Amers in accordance immed preceding msg, which quoted Depts
                    statement re <hi rend="italic">Gen Gordon</hi> Shanghai call.</p>
                <p>For ur confid info: Dept has informed APL that it has clrd the voyage. Other
                    interested govt agencies have concurred this clearance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
